16. triplex Piraei portus: the Piraeus was a rocky peninsula commanded by the height Munychia‚ and had three (triplex) excellent harbors, via the Piraeus in the narrower sense, and two smaller ones, Aphrodisia (Munychia) and Zea (see rnap opposite p. 9). Themistocles began this work in 4824 as archon, but, owing to interruption and injury from the Persians, the walls were not completed till 477, when the Piraeus had a complete circumvallation of its own, and was connected by “the long walls” with the city, about four miles away.
